This involves the acceptance of Lipsius's sex et qumquaginta. Thus at 17. 22 reference is made to the last largess which had been given to the people (proxima quedem congiaria ipsi uidistis plerosque senes, tec.) as something within recent memory: it is known to have been given by Titus in 73.
